  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat.",
    "2. In a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce, ginger, and sesame oil.",
    "3. Add the pre-cooked barbacoa beef to the bowl and marinate for at least 10 minutes.",
    "4. Grill the beef for 2-3 minutes per side, or until slightly charred.",
    "5. Warm tortillas by wrapping them in a damp paper towel and microwaving for 20-30 seconds.",
    "6. Assemble tacos by slicing the grilled beef and placing it onto a warmed tortilla.",
    "7. Top with green onions, sesame seeds, and cilantro.",
    "8. Serve with lime wedges on the side."
